  <div class="wrapper">
    <div class="awards">
      <img src="img/awards.png" alt="awards" />
    </div>
    <div class="section">
      <h2>Time to say goodbye ðŸ‘‹</h2>
      <p>
        We've had an incredible time building Neverthink,
        but our journey has now come to an end.
        We hope you enjoyed watching Neverthink as
        much as we did creating it.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="section">
      <h2 class="f2">Stats</h2>
      <div class="stats">
        <div><h3 class="c1">15M</h3><p>Users wordwide</p></div>
        <div><h3 class="c2">85K</h3><p>Creators</p></div>
        <div><h3 class="c1">300</h3><p>Partners</p></div>
        <div><h3 class="c3">700M</h3><p>Total video views</p></div>
        <div><h3 class="c3">5M</h3><p>Videos reviewed by our team</p></div>
        <div><h3 class="c2">500K</h3><p>Videos selected by our team</p></div>
      </div>

    </div>
    <div class="section">
      <a href="https://memeinsider.com/releases/the-state-of-the-video-meme-industry" class="quote">
        <span class="quote-text">With strong backing of people who truly love and understand meme culture. Neverthink is poised to become a major player in the world of memes</span>
        <span class="quote-source">Meme Insider</span>
      </a>
      <a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/jacksonweimer/2021/05/27/the-new-video-platform-for-watching-high-quality-memes-neverthinktv/?sh=55b0b33e32ab" class="quote">
        <span class="quote-text">The New Video Platform For Watching High-Quality Memes: Neverthink.TV</span>
        <span class="quote-source">Forbes</span>
      </a>
    </div>
    <div class="section">
      <h2 class="f2">The team</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        {% for user in team | sort(false, false, 'name') %}
          <div class="grid-item">
            <img class="grid-image" src="{{ user.image }}" alt="{{ user.name }}"/>
            <span class="grid-name">{{ user.name }}</span>
            <span class="grid-title">{{ user.title }}</span>
          </div>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section">
      <h2 class="f2">Our partners</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        {% for user in partners | sort(false, false, 'name') %}
          <div class="grid-item">
            <img class="grid-image" src="{{ user.profileImageUrl }}" alt="{{ user.publicName }}"/>
            <span class="grid-name">{{ user.publicName }}</span>
          </div>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
